Next.js 16 (App Router) with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS v4, deployed on Vercel.

## Develop

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:3000.

## Environment

Copy the repository-level `.env.example` to `.env.local` and fill in the values.
The app reads:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` for the
  browser and server Supabase clients. Both respect Row Level Security.
- A `sb_secret_*` key only when a server route must bypass RLS. Keep it out of
  any `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variable.
- `MODAL_ENDPOINT_URL`, `MODAL_TOKEN`, and `MODAL_CALLBACK_TOKEN` when the Modal
  compute seam is enabled.

## Layout

- `app/` holds routes, the root layout, and API route handlers.
- `lib/supabase/` wires the browser client, the cookie-bound server client, and
  the middleware session refresh.
- `middleware.ts` refreshes the auth session on every matched request.
- `app/api/health` returns the environment, version, and commit for quick checks.
